<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14393</anchor> <rss>jms-00BW.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00BW</addr>  <route>jms-00BW.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Computation paths</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em>computation path</em> is defined to be a finite <link href="jms-00BV.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BV" title="Elementary event structures">elementary</link> <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structure</link>; we define the category of computation paths to be the full subcategory of <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structures</link> and <link href="jms-00BR.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BR" title="Rigid morphisms of event structures">rigid maps</link> spanned by computation paths.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14394</anchor> <rss>jms-00BU.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00BU</addr>  <route>jms-00BU.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>A subcategory of <link href="jms-00BW.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BW" title="Computation paths">computation paths</link></title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14395</anchor> <rss>jms-00BV.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00BV</addr>  <route>jms-00BV.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Elementary event structures</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structure</link> is called <em>elementary</em> when every finite set of events is <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">consistent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14396</anchor> <rss>jms-00BW.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00BW</addr>  <route>jms-00BW.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Computation paths</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em>computation path</em> is defined to be a finite <link href="jms-00BV.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BV" title="Elementary event structures">elementary</link> <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structure</link>; we define the category of computation paths to be the full subcategory of <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structures</link> and <link href="jms-00BR.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BR" title="Rigid morphisms of event structures">rigid maps</link> spanned by computation paths.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14397</anchor> <rss>jms-00BX.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Remark</taxon> <addr>jms-00BX</addr>  <route>jms-00BX.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Rigid morphisms between computation paths</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="jms-00BW.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BW" title="Computation paths">computation path</link> is clearly same thing as a finite poset. A <link href="jms-00BR.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BR" title="Rigid morphisms of event structures">rigid morphism</link> between computation paths corresponds, however, to a <em>monomorphism</em> of posets (not necessarily regular).</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14398</anchor> <rss>jms-00BV.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00BV</addr>  <route>jms-00BV.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Elementary event structures</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structure</link> is called <em>elementary</em> when every finite set of events is <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">consistent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14399</anchor> <rss>jms-00BN.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00BN</addr>  <route>jms-00BN.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Event structure</title>  <meta name="source"><link href="staton-winskel-2010.xml" type="local" addr="staton-winskel-2010" title="On the expressivity of symmetry in event structures">[staton-winskel-2010]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em>event structure</em> is defined to be triple <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( E, \mathsf { Con } _{ E } ,  \leq _E \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex> where <tex>E</tex> is a partial order of <em>events</em> partially ordered by the <em>causal dependency relation</em> <tex>\leq _E</tex>, and <tex>\mathsf { Con } _{ E } \subseteq   \mathcal {P} _{ \mathit {fin} } { \mathopen {} \left ( E \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex> specifies when a finite subset of <tex>E</tex> is <em>consistent</em>, satisfying the following laws:</p><ol><li>every downset of <tex>E</tex> is finite;</li>
  <li>every singleton set is consistent;</li>
  <li>any subset of a consistent subset is consistent;</li>
  <li>for any consistent subset <tex>x \in \mathsf { Con } _{ E }</tex> and <tex>e \leq  e'</tex> with <tex>e' \in  x</tex>, we have <tex>x \cup { \mathopen {} \left \{ e \right \} \mathclose {}} \in \mathsf { Con } _{ E }</tex>.</li></ol></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14400</anchor> <rss>jms-00BR.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00BR</addr>  <route>jms-00BR.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Rigid morphisms of <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structures</link></title>  <meta name="source"><link href="staton-winskel-2010.xml" type="local" addr="staton-winskel-2010" title="On the expressivity of symmetry in event structures">[staton-winskel-2010]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em>rigid morphism</em> of <link href="jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structures</link> <tex>{ E } \xrightarrow {{ f }}{ E' }</tex> is a monotone function on events that preserves finite <link href="jms-00BO.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BO" title="Configurations of an event structure">configurations</link> and is <em>locally injective</em> in the sense that for any finite <link href="jms-00BO.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BO" title="Configurations of an event structure">configuration</link> <tex>x \in \mathcal {C} _{ E }^{ \mathit {fin} }</tex> and events <tex>e_1,e_2 \in  x</tex> such that <tex>fe_1 = fe_2</tex>, we have <tex>e_1=e_2</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14401</anchor> <rss>jms-00BU.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00BU</addr>  <route>jms-00BU