jms-00BN.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BN" title="Event structure">event structures</link> and <link href="jms-00BR.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BR" title="Rigid morphisms of event structures">rigid maps</link> spanned by computation paths.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14404</anchor> <rss>jms-00BX.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Remark</taxon> <addr>jms-00BX</addr>  <route>jms-00BX.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Rigid morphisms between computation paths</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="jms-00BW.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BW" title="Computation paths">computation path</link> is clearly same thing as a finite poset. A <link href="jms-00BR.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BR" title="Rigid morphisms of event structures">rigid morphism</link> between computation paths corresponds, however, to a <em>monomorphism</em> of posets (not necessarily regular).</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>14405</anchor> <rss>jms-00BX.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Remark</taxon> <addr>jms-00BX</addr>  <route>jms-00BX.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Rigid morphisms between computation paths</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="jms-00BW.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BW" title="Computation paths">computation path</link> is clearly same thing as a finite poset. A <link href="jms-00BR.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00BR" title="Rigid morphisms of event structures">rigid morphism</link> between computation paths corresponds, however, to a <em>monomorphism</em> of posets (not necessarily regular).</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>